{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> αἰσχύνω</b> [ῡ]: <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>imperfect</i> αἰσχύνεσκε (κατ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD(?): Quintus Smyrnaeus Epicus 14.531\">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]: <i>future</i> <b>-ῠνῶ</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 719\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>-υνέω</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.53\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ᾔσχῡνα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.571, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 1.4, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> σχυγκα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 58.16\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> αἰσχῠνοῦμαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 856, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 200, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 49d, etc., rarely αἰσχυνθήσομαι (see. entry near the end)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ᾐσχύνθην[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] and <i>Attic dialect</i>, <i>poetry</i> <i>infinitive</i> αἰσχυνθῆμεν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 9.27: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> ᾔσχυμμαι (see. below [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus I)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>make ugly, disfigure</b>, πρόσωπον, κόμην, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.24, 27, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 529\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; αἰ. τὸν ἵππον <b>give</b> the horse <b>a bad form</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 1.12. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> mostly in moral sense, <b>dishonour, tarnish</b>, μηδὲ γένος πατέρων αἰσχυνέμεν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.209, compare 23.571; τὴν Σπάρτην 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.53; ξενίαν τράπεζαν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 401; τοὺς πρὸς αἵματος 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1305; τοὺς πατέρας 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Menexenus” 246d. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> especially <b>dishonour</b> a woman, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 44, compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Marcellus” 19, etc.; εὐνήν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1626\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς τὸ σῶμα αἰ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1311b7; _absolutely_, “Foed. Delph.Pell.” 2 A 12. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>disdain</b>, ἐπιχώρια[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.22. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__B</b></Level1> <i>passive</i>, <b>to be dishonoured</b>, νέκυς σχυμμένος, of Patroclus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.180. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.II</b></Level2> <b>to be ashamed, feel shame</b>, <i>absolutely</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.305, 18.12, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.10, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 1291. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.2</b></Level3> more commonly, <b>to be ashamed at</b> a thing, with <i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i>, αἰσχυνόμενοι φάτιν ἀνδρῶν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.323; τὴν δυσγένειαν τὴν ἐμὴν αἰ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1079: with _dative_ _of things_, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 992, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 3.9, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 4.42, etc.; αἰ. ἐπί τινι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.2.8; ἔν τινι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.43; ὑπέρ τινος 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 14.39; περί τινος 33.6. etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__B.II.2.b</b></Level4> with <i>participle</i>, <b>to be ashamed at</b> doing a thing (which one does), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 642 (variant), 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 540, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 200, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Grg.” 494e, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__B.II.2.c</b></Level4> with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>to be ashamed to</b> do a thing (and therefore not to do it), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.82, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 856, “Ch.” 917, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 414e, “Phdr.” 257d, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; though this condition must not be pressed absolutely,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare “Ap.” 22b. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__B.II.2.d</b></Level4> followed by <i>relative</i> clause, αἰσχύνεσθαι εἰ.. <b>to be ashamed</b> that.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 254, 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.42; ἐάν.. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 21.4; μὴ.. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 183e, cf. Machoap. 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 13.579f; ὅτι.. 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 2.23. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.3</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i>, <b>to feel shame before</b> one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 934, 1074, 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 23.6, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 216b\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοὺς γέροντας (at Sparta) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.180\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὅστις γὰρ αὐτὸς αὑτὸν οὐκ αἰσχύνεται, πῶστόν γε μηδὲν εἰδότ᾽ αἰσχυνθήσετα; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 229, compare 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 5.26\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 415; ᾑσχύνθημεν θεοὺς.. προδοῦναι αὐτόν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.3.22; αἰσχύνομαι ὑμᾶς λέγειν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 40.48; αἰ. πρός τινα 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1383b12.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0153","accentedUnicode":"αἰσχύνω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0148","matchingForm":"αἰσχρολογία","stepTransliteration":"aischrologia","gloss":"obscenity","_zh_tw_Gloss":"污穢言語","_es_Gloss":"obscenidad ","_zh_Gloss":"污秽言语"},{"strongNumber":"G0150","matchingForm":"αἰσχρός","stepTransliteration":"aischros","gloss":"shameful","_zh_tw_Gloss":"羞愧","_es_Gloss":"vergonzoso","_zh_Gloss":"羞愧"},{"strongNumber":"G0151","matchingForm":"αἰσχρότης","stepTransliteration":"aischrotēs","gloss":"obscenity","_zh_tw_Gloss":"淫穢","_es_Gloss":"obscenidad ","_zh_Gloss":"淫秽"},{"strongNumber":"G0152","matchingForm":"αἰσχύνη","stepTransliteration":"aischunē","gloss":"shame","_zh_tw_Gloss":"羞辱","_es_Gloss":"vergüenza","_zh_Gloss":"羞辱"},{"strongNumber":"G0422","matchingForm":"ἀνεπαίσχυντος","stepTransliteration":"anepaischuntos","gloss":"unashamed","_zh_tw_Gloss":"無愧","_es_Gloss":"no avergonzado","_zh_Gloss":"无愧"},{"strongNumber":"G1870","matchingForm":"ἐπαισχύνομαι","stepTransliteration":"epaischunomai","gloss":"be ashamed of","_zh_tw_Gloss":"當作可恥","_es_Gloss":"estar avergonzado ","_zh_Gloss":"当作可耻"},{"strongNumber":"G2617","matchingForm":"καταισχύνω","stepTransliteration":"kataischunō","gloss":"to dishonor","_zh_tw_Gloss":"羞愧","_es_Gloss":"deshonrar","_zh_Gloss":"羞愧"}],"shortDef":"to be ashamed, dishonored, <ref='2Co.10.8'>2Co.10.8</ref>; <ref='Php.1.20, 1'>Php.1.20, 1</ref>Pe.4.16, <ref='1Jn.2.28'>